<div id="review_4042363965" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4042363965" />
    <a title="Erik Graff" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/974210-erik-graff"><img alt="Erik Graff" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1299888977p2/974210.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4042363965?book_show_action=true">Jun 05, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erik Graff" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erik Graff" href="/user/show/974210-erik-graff">Erik Graff</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780716733874" href="/book/show/263643.Why_People_Believe_Weird_Things">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">fringe science fans</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Erik by: </span>
      no one
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/974210-erik-graff?shelf=sciences">sciences</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4042363965" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5977030298669403214">The author evolved from being a theologically-trained, believing Christian to becoming a leader of the Skeptics Society. This book consists of essays about such pseudo-sciences as Objectivism, Creation-science, Holocaust-denial, UFOlogy and the like. For me the most interesting part was his review of the Holocaust debate, the most disappointing his treatment of what our government now calls &apos;unidentified aerial phenomena&apos;. Throughout Shermer maintains a sense of humor and tolerance.</span>
  <span id="freeText5977030298669403214" style="display:none">The author evolved from being a theologically-trained, believing Christian to becoming a leader of the Skeptics Society. This book consists of essays about such pseudo-sciences as Objectivism, Creation-science, Holocaust-denial, UFOlogy and the like. For me the most interesting part was his review of the Holocaust debate, the most disappointing his treatment of what our government now calls 'unidentified aerial phenomena'. Throughout Shermer maintains a sense of humor and tolerance.</span>
